      "content": "I can see why you're tempted to try a lower dose, but I would strongly advise against it. Taking 250mg of ciprofloxacin is still a significant amount, and reducing the dose doesn't necessarily make it safe. The American College of Obstetricians and Gynecologists recommends avoiding fluoroquinolones during pregnancy altogether, regardless of dosage. Instead, I would recommend waiting for your midwife appointment and following her guidance, as she can assess the situation and provide the best advice for you and your baby.",
